      question: 'How much test coverage do we actually need?',
      answer: 'There is no single right number, and chasing 100 percent coverage is usually wasteful. We focus coverage where the risk and value are highest: critical revenue paths, complex business logic and anything that has caused production incidents before. A pragmatic target for most teams is strong end-to-end coverage of the handful of journeys that matter most, solid integration tests around service boundaries, and unit tests concentrated on logic-heavy code rather than trivial getters and setters.',
